Hypothesis 1

friends_vs_happiness <- responses %>% select(Number.of.friends, Happiness.in.life) %>% arrange(desc(Number.of.friends))

xyplot( Number.of.friends ~ Happiness.in.life, data = friends_vs_happiness, main="", jitter.x=TRUE, jitter.y=TRUE)

There appears to be a positive relationship between number of friends and happiness in life. The more friends you have, the happier you are.

Hypothesis 2

gender_vs_happiness <- responses %>% select(Gender, Happiness.in.life) %>% na.omit()

bwplot( Happiness.in.life ~ Gender, data = gender_vs_happiness, main="")

There doesnt appear to be a relationship between gender and happiness, as the plots for both genders are the same

Hypothesis 3

happiness_vs_age <- responses %>% select(Age, Happiness.in.life) %>% na.omit() %>% group_by(Age) %>% summarise(avg_happiness = mean(Happiness.in.life))

xyplot( avg_happiness ~ Age, data = happiness_vs_age, main="")

There appears to be a positive relationship between age group and average happiness. As age increases, so does average happiness.

Hypothesis 4

height_vs_weight <- responses %>% select(Height, Weight) %>% na.omit() %>% group_by(Weight)

 xyplot( Weight ~ Height, data = height_vs_weight, main="")

As height increases, so does weight.

Hypothesis 5

partying_vs_alcohol <- responses %>% select(Entertainment.spending, Alcohol) %>% na.omit() %>% group_by(Entertainment.spending)

 bwplot( Entertainment.spending ~ Alcohol, data = partying_vs_alcohol, main="")

It was surprising to see that people classified themeselves as social drinkers reported spending as much money as people who never drink. It made sense that people who reported drinking a lot, spent the most money on entertainment.

Hypothesis 6

heights_vs_flying <- responses %>% select(Heights, Flying) %>% na.omit() %>% group_by(Heights) %>% summarise(avg_flying = mean(Flying))

xyplot( avg_flying ~ Heights, data = heights_vs_flying, main="", jitter.x=TRUE, jitter.y=TRUE)

As expected, the groups of people who were more afraid of heights, were on average, more afraid of flying.
